condition: Improve my relationship with my child
message_text: @fields.age_group_for_tips
@fields.child_nickname

Quick tip: When you give your baby your full attention, you make them feel secure and loved. Try to spend at least 20 minutes a day playing with @fields.child_nickname. Switch off the television and put away phones. Make it fun!

Quick tip: When you give your baby your full attention, you make them feel secure and loved. Try to spend at least 20 minutes a day playing with your baby. Switch off the television and put away phones. Make it fun!
@fields.child_nickname

Quick tip: Spending time with your child is free and even 5 minutes a day can make a difference. Try asking @fields.child_nickname what they would like to do together. It can be fun and relaxing for you too!
Quick tip: Spending time with your child is free and even 5 minutes a day can make a difference. Try asking your child what they would like to do together. It can be fun and relaxing for you too!
@fields.child_nickname

Quick tip: All children misbehave. One thing that can help is to praise @fields.child_nickname anytime that they do something good – however small. They may not look like they want your praise but they still really, really do.

Quick tip: All children misbehave. One thing that can help is to praise your child anytime that they do something good – however small. They may not look like they want your praise but they still really, really do.

condition: My child to do better at school
message_text: Quick tip: It is really hard to help our children continue learning when schools are closed or part-open. One thing that might be helpful is to try and set up a daily schedule that includes time for schoolwork and time for fun.

condition: To talk to my child about COVID-19
message_text:
Quick tip: It can be difficult to know how to talk to your children about something like COVID-19, especially since we are learning about it too. 

The important thing is to be open and listen to your children. Be honest and supportive. Show them that you care.

condition: Feel less stress, loneliness or anger
message_text: Quick tip: Caring for yourself is really important. Take five deep breaths when you feel overwhelmed. Try talking to a friend, or doing something relaxing for yourself? You deserve it!

Quick tip: It is normal to be stressed about money. Talk to your children about how much money comes in and what you spend money on as a family each month. When everyone sees where the money goes, it is easier to agree on where you can save money together!

Quick tip: This is a stressful time for all of us. When a problem comes up, talk about it together! What is the problem exactly? What different solutions are there and what are the consequences of one? That way, you can find a solution that can be OK for everyone.

condition: Know more about how to keep my child safe
message_text: @fields.child_nickname

Quick tip: Try to start a conversation with @fields.child_nickname about safe and unsafe places in your community and online. They may even know some you don’t. This will help you make a plan together about how to stay safe.

We hope this small tip will help. More support will be given later on when we talk about keeping my child safe.

condition: How to support children living with disabilities
message_text: Quick tip: All children, including those living with disabilities, need love, respect and time especially at difficult times.
